5:
Welcome back. I'm glad you came
without any... extra encouragement.
9:
*Sigh* We received payment in full.
Fair is fair.
14:
I could finally afford to make
macarons. Here, try one, Quazer.
18:
Why, thank you! What a precious
design. I'll display it proudly.
22: But I made it for eating?
26:
What a waste! I would rather keep it
for my collection.
30:
Would it happen to come with the
chef, by any chance?
35: Stop trying to claim us all!
45:
Drawn by these precious creatures,
were you? Too bad I'm not the
sharing type!
60:
What do we do! We can't abandon
Light!
64:
I need buffoons who know these
waters. But not a peep about the
sea monster or any ships it may
have wrecked, got it?
67:
Money is no object. As per usual, I
will have what I seek, no matter the
cost.
71:
So the beast that whisked my lovely
hero away makes its lair on a
deserted island...
73:
So? How much do you imbeciles
want to retrieve him?
77: Wow, even the pirates are scared...
81:
They want easy profits. Crooks will
be crooks; why risk your neck for a
hero?
86:
...We're running out of time. Let me
goâ€”I'll save him myself!
91:
I'm sure this won't endear him to me,
but...
95:
Fine. I have orders you lot should be
able to manage: spread the story
that there's treasure on that island.
And make sure it spreads far.
100: Land ho! The island's straight ahead!
102:
Heh-heh-heh! I smell bounty on the
sea breeze, mateys! Today's our
lucky day!
104:
Cap'n, haven't you heard the
rumors? There's tell of a kraken
about!
106:
Bah, that's just pub talk, spread to
keep us from our goal. We have to
get there before the landlubber who
spread the rumors in the first place!
108:
Ahh, I can taste the doubloons
already! Ready the anchor, mateysâ€”
114:
I wonder how many ships it sank
today.
118:
Sounds like you wanted it to sink a
whole armada...
122:
They're just stupid, ugly pirates. I'll
have my men rescue them... for a
fee.
126:
But at least they were useful. A
brilliant distraction, and enough of
them to repeat the tactic as many
times as we need.
131:
You pathetic creature. You played
right into my hand.
136:
Aww, my adorable hero. You will
never escape me again...
139:
Wh-what! The sea devil's already
dead!
141:
The treasure is finally ours! Haha!
Sorry if you thought YOU were going
to get it.
156:
You are unbelievably vicious. More
dangerous than any fiend.
160:
Aww, you don't appreciate being
saved?
164:
Personally, I can't stand you. But I
also won't deny that you rescued
me.
167:
As much as I despise your methods,
it seems there are still things I can
learn from you.
180:
Ah, I hate when you act like you can
help yourself. It breaks my fantasy.
182:
If you want, I could reveal that
fantasy to you. Every little bit, until
you know me inside and out.
186:
Sounds like a fate worse than death.
Alk, we're going!
191:
Aww, he truly is the most adorable
thing.
